#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn49.23-34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 49 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 49 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:0.2"
msgid "3. Balakaraṇīyavagga "
msgstr "3. Hard Work "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:0.3"
msgid "23–34. Balakaraṇīyādisutta "
msgstr "23–34. Hard Work, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.246, sc1
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci balakaraṇīyā kammantā kayiranti, sabbe te pathaviṃ nissāya pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhāya evamete balakaraṇīyā kammantā kayiranti; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, all the hard work that gets done depends on the earth and is grounded on the earth. "

msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya cattāro sammappadhāne bhāveti, cattāro sammappadhāne bahulīkaroti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant develops and cultivates the four right efforts depending on and grounded on ethics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.3"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya cattāro sammappadhāne bhāveti, cattāro sammappadhāne bahulīkaroti? "
msgstr "How so? "

msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati … pe … "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. … "

msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.5"
msgid "uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati. "
msgstr "so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are completed by development. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlaṃ nissāya sīle patiṭṭhāya cattāro sammappadhāne bhāveti, cattāro sammappadhāne bahulīkarotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant develops and cultivates the four right efforts depending on and grounded on ethics.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.7"
msgid "(Evaṃ balakaraṇīyavaggo sammappadhānavasena vitthāretabbo.) "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 45.149–160.) "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.8"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:1.9"
msgid "Balakaraṇīyavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:2.1"
msgid "Balaṃ bījañca nāgo ca, "
msgstr "Hard work, seeds, and dragons, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:2.2"
msgid "rukkho kumbhena sūkiyā; "
msgstr "a tree, a pot, and a spike, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:2.3"
msgid "Ākāsena ca dve meghā, "
msgstr "the sky, and two on clouds, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn49.23-34:2.4"
msgid "nāvā āgantukā nadīti. "
msgstr "a ship, a guest house, and a river."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
